N:ai-tool-compliance
D:Verifies internal AI tool implementation against P0/P1 mandatory rules. Scans codebase for auth, security, cost, and logging compliance. Supports slash mode aliases /quick, /full, /improve. Produces risk scores and remediation tasks and gates deployments on P0 violations.
G:compliance verification p0 rules auth security cost logging audit governance gate deployment quick full improve compliance-quick compliance-full compliance-improve slash-command

U[5]:
  /quick mode for fast P0 signal scan after implementation changes
  /full mode for release gating with full compliance verification
  /improve mode for remediation loop on failed rules
  Generate compliance score reports for audits
  Identify specific rule violations with file:line evidence

S[7]{n,action,details}:
  1,Route,Resolve slash mode aliases: /quick->scan /full->verify /improve->improve
  2,Load,Read rules/p0-catalog.yaml — parse all 11 P0 rules with check patterns and targets
  3,Scan,Glob project files matching check_targets — collect candidate files per rule
  4,Analyze,Grep check_patterns on candidates — determine must_contain/must_not_contain matches
  5,Judge,Apply Pass/Fail/Warning/N/A verdict per rule based on pattern match results
  6,Score,Calculate fixed-point risk score: 보안(35) + 권한(30) + 비용(20) + 로그(15) = 100점 만점
  7,Report,Generate risk-score-report.md + remediation-task.json for each Fail — gate exit code

R[4]:
  Never modify source code — this skill is verification-only (Read, Grep, Glob, Bash)
  Mark rules as N/A when grep_patterns find no matching code — do not penalize unused features
  Always include file:line evidence for every Fail and Warning verdict
  P0 Fail on any single rule blocks deployment gate (exit 1) — no exceptions
